freetext.SYMPTOMS_DESCRIPTION: Developed painful earache last Friday despite seeing no one but my husband. Saw doc 2x. Taking decongestant to unplug ear and using prescription nasal spray.

Do not know if this is related, but on 3 different days I had a feeling of having been punched in the upper back. Once it caused me to lay down before finishing getting ready for bed. But mostly, if I took it easy for a bit it went away.
Flare of carpal tunnel I did not realize I had. Very painful.

I have occasional mildly swollen glands in my neck. I am strictly secluding and wonder if it might relate to the vaccine. It is not great cause for concern.I had a brief bout of diarrhea a couple days ago.
The carpal tunnel flare is still bad. Icing, wearing hard brace day, soft brace night.

freetext.SYSTEMIC_REACTION_OTHER: Dizziness on left side of head, while seated. It went away, but felt unusual.
In retrospect I wonder if the stiff shoulder neck area of last couple days was related to vaccine. It is better today.
